blog.name: surferofrowdybliss
blog.title: Visual Play
blog.description:
Deborah Coulter

Scissors in hand, I make collages exploring the freedom and fun of visual play. I get lost in the joy of selecting, cutting, and rearranging images. The process begins as I discover the infinite possibilities life offers through the spaciousness of an open heart. Children, animals, and nature lead the way.

I invite you to join me in these adventures of scissors & glue blending with imagination in the exquisite present.

https://instagram.com/deborahcoulterartflow/

http://society6.com/deborahcoulter

summary: ©Deborah Coulter 2018 Collage for week of the full moon...fireflies floating in waves of full moon glow. Flashback Friday I made...
caption:
©Deborah Coulter 2018

Collage for week of the full moon…fireflies floating in waves of full moon glow.

Flashback Friday

I made this collage during the summer solstice in 2013. Upon awakening from a nap as the moon was rising, I was surrounded by fireflies. For a few moments it felt as if I had floated up to the stars while sleeping. It began to drizzle and instantly I was brought back into the glow of summer magic.
